
*** HOW TO INSTALL TRON LIBS

> INTRODUCTION

This document explains how to install tron libs for robotic control.

Software requirements:
- Linux environment
- Netbeans 8.1 for C++
- git


> INSTALLATION


1. Download tron

git clone https://github.com/albarral/tron.git


2. Build tron_test project (in Netbeans)


3. Make tron libs accessible from everywhere:

cd <tron_installation_path>
gedit tron.conf
change paths to meet real tron installation 

sudo mv tron.conf /etc/ld.so.conf.d
sudo /sbin/ldconfig


4. Prepare config files for tron logging:

see instructions in file logging/README_tron_logging
located in <tron_installation_path>





